vectorData.altText: 12. The group of lymph nodes located anterior to the ears are the _______________ nodes.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.
That's right!  The preauricular (parotid) nodes are the group of lymph nodes located anterior to the ears.

Lymphatic vessels from the scalp and face follow the arteries. They eventually reach a superficial group of nodes that form a ring around the base of the skull. These nodes cluster into several groups, the names of which are regional and therefore intuitive. 
These are the:
occipital nodes
retroauricular (mastoid) nodes
preauricular (parotid) nodes
submandibular nodes
submental nodes
